ard**: Left swipe = undefined/nothing, right swipe = delete only\n- **ReviewTaskCard**: Right = done, left = skip, down = delete\n\nUsers can't build a reliable mental model.\n\n### 16. Right-swipe buttons are non-functional\n`SwipableTaskCard.tsx:247-273` — Bell and Flag buttons in the swipe reveal call `console.log(\"pressed\")` only. They occupy prime interaction space but do nothing.\n\n### 17. Task completion toast only shows for public tasks\n`SwipableTaskCard.tsx:150-164` — Toast feedback only appears if `task.public === true`. Private task completions have zero visual feedback.\n\n### 18. Ghost block confirmation in CalendarView is undiscoverable\n`CalendarView.tsx:187-205` — Users must tap *within* a ghost block (±12px tolerance) to confirm it. No \"Tap to confirm\" text. Tapping outside silently dismisses it.\n\n### 19. Modal stacking goes 3 layers deep\n`EncourageModal.tsx` and `CongratulateModal.tsx` can stack: DefaultModal → GIF Picker (native Modal) → CustomAlert. Users lose track of which layer they're on.\n\n### 20. Profile edit and Settings have overlapping notification toggles\n`(profile)/edit.tsx:300-321` has Activity, Push Notifications, and Today's Tasks toggles. `(task)/settings.tsx` has separate notification settings (check-in frequency). Users won't find all settings in one place.\n\n### 21. Today screen tells users to navigate elsewhere to add tasks\n`today.tsx:47-50` — Subtitle says \"feel free to navigate to your workspaces to add new tasks!\" Users should be able to add tasks from THIS screen.\n\n### 22. Password requirements not shown upfront\n`(onboarding)/password.tsx:102-104` — No requirements text visible until the user starts typing, when a helper shows \"X more characters needed.\" Users don't know the 8-char minimum beforehand.\n\n### 23. Two different blueprint creation entry points\n- `/blueprint/create` (standalone, hides tab bar)\n- `/(feed,search,profile)/blueprint/[id]` (nested under shared layout, keeps tab bar)\n\nUsers don't know which path they're on or why navigation differs.\n\n### 24. Mixed feed content (Posts + Tasks) without clear labels\n`feed.tsx:167-180` — Feed shows both \"posts\" and \"task completions\" interleaved without clear type indicators. Users don't understand what content appears or why.\n\n### 25. Dismiss paths differ: swipe-down vs button\n`CustomAlert.tsx:53-57` and `QueuedAlert.tsx:44-47` — Both disable pan-down-to-close. Users habituated to swiping down to dismiss will feel stuck.\n\n### 26. DeletePreviewModal uses inverted mental model\n`DeletePreviewModal.tsx:105` — Says \"Deselect tasks you want to keep.\" Users expect to *select* what to delete, not deselect what to keep.\n\n### 27. Onboarding state not persisted\nIf a user closes the app mid-onboarding, all progress is lost. `useOnboarding` stores state in-memory only — no AsyncStorage backup.\n\n### 28. Activity tab icon (Brain) doesn't match its purpose\n`(tabs)/_layout.tsx:252-260` — Uses a Brain icon for \"Activity.\" Brain typically signals AI/insights, not activity history. The icon also has no visual change when selected.\n\n---\n\n## Low Severity\n\n### 29. `friends/[id].tsx` route is broken\nReferences undefined `isLoading` and `error` variables. Navigation to this route will error.\n\n### 30. \"Finish Kindred Onboarding\" task feels redundant\n`accomplishment.tsx:256-257` — The user just finished onboarding, then is asked to swipe-complete a hardcoded \"Finish Onboarding\" task. Feels circular.\n\n### 31. Notifications screen named \"notifications.tsx\" does no notification permission request\n`(onboarding)/notifications.tsx:42-49` — Title says \"Welcome!\" but the file is named `notifications`. No actual permission request happens.\n\n### 32. FloatingDateNav uses magic pixel value\n`FloatingDateNav.tsx:223` — `bottom: 100` is a hardcoded pixel value. Will misalign on devices with different tab bar heights or safe areas.\n\n### 33. Playground routes accessible in codebase but unreachable from