ime, loc *time.Location) time.Time {\n\treturn now.Add(5 * time.Minute).In(time.UTC)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update unit tests**\n\nIn `flex_period_test.go`, update the three `ComputeCooldown` tests. For each test, the expected result should be `now.Add(5 * time.Minute).In(time.UTC)` instead of the old values.\n\nFor `TestDailyFlexPeriod_ComputeCooldown` (around line 46):\n```go\nfunc TestDailyFlexPeriod_ComputeCooldown(t *testing.T) {\n\td := DailyFlexPeriod{}\n\tnow := time.Date(2025, 6, 15, 10, 30, 0, 0, time.UTC)\n\tcooldown := d.ComputeCooldown(now, time.UTC)\n\texpected := now.Add(5 * time.Minute).In(time.UTC)\n\tassert.Equal(t, expected, cooldown)\n}\n```\n\nFor `TestWeeklyFlexPeriod_ComputeCooldown` (around line 91):\n```go\nfunc TestWeeklyFlexPeriod_ComputeCooldown(t *testing.T) {\n\tw := WeeklyFlexPeriod{}\n\t// Wednesday 2025-06-18\n\tnow := time.Date(2025, 6, 18, 14, 0, 0, 0, time.UTC)\n\tcooldown := w.ComputeCooldown(now, time.UTC)\n\texpected := now.Add(5 * time.Minute).In(time.UTC)\n\tassert.Equal(t, expected, cooldown)\n}\n```\n\nFor `TestMonthlyFlexPeriod_ComputeCooldown` (around line 144):\n```go\nfunc TestMonthlyFlexPeriod_ComputeCooldown(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := MonthlyFlexPeriod{}\n\tnow := time.Date(2025, 6, 15, 10, 30, 0, 0, time.UTC)\n\tcooldown := m.ComputeCooldown(now, time.UTC)\n\texpected := now.Add(5 * time.Minute).In(time.UTC)\n\tassert.Equal(t, expected, cooldown)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run tests**\n\nRun: `cd /Users/abhik.ray/Kindred/backend && go test ./internal/handlers/task/ -run \"ComputeCooldown\" -v`\nExpected: All 3 cooldown tests PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add backend/internal/handlers/task/flex_period_daily.go backend/internal/handlers/task/flex_period_weekly.go backend/internal/handlers/task/flex_period_monthly.go backend/internal/handlers/task/flex_period_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat: reduce flex task cooldown to 5 minutes\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Backend — Inline Spawn Next Flex Instance on