ID: updatedTemplate.CategoryID.Hex(),\n\t}, nil\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Update CompleteTask to propagate NextFlexTask**\n\nIn `service.go` around lines 400-405, update the flex completion call site:\n\nReplace:\n```go\n\t\t\tif template.RecurType == \"FLEX\" && template.FlexState != nil {\n\t\t\t\tif err := s.handleFlexCompletion(ctx, template); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tslog.Error(\"Failed to handle flex completion\", \"error\", err, \"templateID\", *taskToComplete.TemplateID)\n\t\t\t\t}\n```\n\nWith:\n```go\n\t\t\tif template.RecurType == \"FLEX\" && template.FlexState != nil {\n\t\t\t\tnextFlexTask, err := s.handleFlexCompletion(ctx, template)\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tslog.Error(\"Failed to handle flex completion\", \"error\", err, \"templateID\", *taskToComplete.TemplateID)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tflexResult = nextFlexTask\n```\n\nAlso add `var flexResult *NextFlexTaskInfo` near the top of the template handling block (before the `if taskToComplete.TemplateID != nil` on line 357), and update the return at the end (around line 459):\n\n```go\n\treturn &TaskCompletionResult{\n\t\tStreakChanged: streakChanged,\n\t\tCurrentStreak: userAfter.Streak,\n\t\tTasksComplete: userAfter.TasksComplete,\n\t\tNextFlexTask:  flexResult,\n\t}, nil\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update CompleteTaskOutput to include next flex task**\n\nIn `operations.go` (around line 82), update the output struct:\n\n```go\ntype CompleteTaskOutput struct {\n\tBody struct {\n\t\tMessage       string           `json:\"message\" example:\"Task completed successfully\"`\n\t\tStreakChanged bool             `json:\"streakChanged\" example:\"true\" doc:\"Indicates if the user's streak increased\"`\n\t\tCurrentStreak int              `json:\"currentStreak\" example:\"5\" doc:\"The user's current streak count\"`\n\t\tTasksComplete float64          `json:\"tasksComplete\" example:\"42\" doc:\"Total tasks completed by user\"`\n\t\tNextFlexTask  *NextFlexTaskDTO `json:\"nextFlexTask,omitempty\" doc:\"If this was a flex task and more instances remain, the next task instance\"`\n\t}\n}\n\ntype NextFlexTaskDTO struct {\n\tTask       TaskDocument `json:\"task\"`\n\tCategoryID string       `json:\"categoryId\"`\n}\n```\n\nNote: `TaskDocument` here refers to `types.TaskDocument`. Import the types package if not already imported in operations.go. Check existing imports — if the file uses `types.TaskDocument` elsewhere, follow that pattern. If it uses a local alias or the huma schema type, match that instead.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Update handler to map the result**\n\nIn `task.go` around lines 411-416, update the handler response mapping:\n\nReplace:\n```go\n\tresp := &CompleteTaskOutput{}\n\tresp.Body.Message = \"Task completed successfully\"\n\tresp.Body.StreakChanged = result.StreakChanged\n\tresp.Body.CurrentStreak = result.CurrentStreak\n\tresp.Body.TasksComplete = result.TasksComplete\n\treturn resp, nil\n```\n\nWith:\n```go\n\tresp := &CompleteTaskOutput{}\n\tresp.Body.Message = \"Task completed successfully\"\n\tresp.Body.StreakChanged = result.StreakChanged\n\tresp.Body.CurrentStreak = result.CurrentStreak\n\tresp.Body.TasksComplete = result.TasksComplete\n\tif result.NextFlexTask != nil {\n\t\tresp.Body.NextFlexTask = &NextFlexTaskDTO{\n\t\t\tTask:       result.NextFlexTask.Task,\n\t\t\tCategoryID: result.NextFlexTask.CategoryID,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn resp, nil\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run all task tests**\n\nRun: `cd /Users/abhik.ray/Kindred/backend && go test ./internal/handlers/task/ -v -timeout 60s`\nExpected: All tests PASS (some flex tests may need adjustment — see next step)\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Fix any broken tests**\n\nThe existing `handleFlexCompletion` test (around line 842 in `service_test.go`) checks `CooldownUntil` is set. Since we now inline-spawn instead of setting cooldown when target is not reached, this assertion may fail. Read the test, understand what it checks, and update it to verify that a new task was created instead.\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Commit**\n\n`