t: insert next flex task into UI immediately on completion\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Update Other Completion Call Sites\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `frontend/hooks/useTaskCompletion.tsx` (if it handles flex tasks)\n- Modify: `frontend/app/(logged-in)/(tabs)/(task)/review.tsx` (review screen completion)\n- Modify: `frontend/components/daily/CalendarView.tsx` (calendar completion)\n\nThere are multiple places that call `markAsCompletedAPI`. Each needs to handle `nextFlexTask` in the response.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Read and update useTaskCompletion hook**\n\nRead `frontend/hooks/useTaskCompletion.tsx` fully. Find where `markAsCompletedAPI` is called (around line 45). After the task is removed from state, insert the next flex task if present in the response. Follow the same pattern as Task 3 Step 2: call `addToCategory` with the returned task.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Read and update review.tsx**\n\nRead `frontend/app/(logged-in)/(tabs)/(task)/review.tsx` around line 179 where `markAsCompletedAPI` is called. Add the same `nextFlexTask` handling. The review screen may not have direct access to `addToCategory` from context — check and add it if needed.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Read and update CalendarView.tsx**\n\nRead `frontend/components/daily/CalendarView.tsx` around line 466 where `markAsCompletedAPI` is called. Add the same `nextFlexTask` handling.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add frontend/hooks/useTaskCompletion.tsx frontend/app/(logged-in)/(tabs)/(task)/review.tsx frontend/components/daily/CalendarView.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat: handle next flex task insert across all completion call sites\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Remove Beta Pill from Login Screen\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `frontend/app/login.tsx:71-82`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Remove the Beta pill View**\n\nIn `frontend/app/login.tsx`, remove lines 71-82 (the `<View>` containing the \"Beta\" text):\n\nRemove this block:\n```tsx\n                <View\n                    style={{\n                        paddingHori