            "content": "# Native Google Sign-In + Auth Error Observability\n\n**Date:** 2026-05-06\n**Status:** Approved\n\n## Summary\n\nReplace the `expo-auth-session/providers/google` implementation with the native `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin` SDK for a more reliable Google Sign-In experience. Simultaneously, improve error observability across all auth flows (Google, Apple, Phone/OTP) by replacing `alert()` calls with toast notifications and adding Sentry error capture.\n\n## Motivation\n\n- Google Sign-In via `expo-auth-session` has redirect URI issues in production builds and requires complex Google Cloud Console configuration. The native SDK eliminates these problems entirely.\n- Auth errors currently use `alert()` (jarring UX) and are not reported to Sentry (invisible to the team).\n- Apple Sign-In works but has the same `alert()`/no-Sentry gaps.\n\n## Part 1: Native Google Sign-In\n\n### Install `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin`\n\nAdd the package and its Expo config plugin. Remove `expo-auth-session/providers/google` usage (keep `expo-auth-session` itself if used elsewhere).\n\n### Config plugin in `app.json`\n\n```json\n[\"@react-native-google-signin/google-signin\", {\n  \"iosUrlScheme\": \"com.googleusercontent.apps.955300435674-4unacg9mbosj1sdf3gqb17lb6rasqmj6\"\n}]\n```\n\n### Rewrite `frontend/hooks/useGoogleAuth.tsx`\n\nReplace internals with native SDK calls while preserving the same external interface:\n\n- `signInAsync()` → returns `GoogleAuthResult` (same shape: `type`, `user`, `idToken`)\n- `loading` → boolean state\n- `userInfo` → current user or null\n\nThe native SDK flow:\n1. Call `GoogleSignin.configure({ iosClientId, webClientId })` on mount\n2. `signInAsync()` calls `GoogleSignin.signIn()` which shows the native bottom-sheet account picker\n3. Extract user info from the response (id, email, name, photo, givenName, familyName)\n4. Return in the existing `GoogleAuthResult` format\n\nNo redirect URIs, no browser, no Expo proxy needed.\n\n### Fix button styling in `OnboardModal.tsx`\n\n- Change `opacity: 0.7` → `1.0` on `googleButton` style (line 471)\n- Remove the comment `\"Slightly dimmed to indicate unavailable\"`\n\n### Clean up\n\n- Remove `GOOGLE_OAUTH_SETUP.md` and `GOOGLE_OAUTH_EXPO_GO_TEST.md` (now obsolete)\n- Remove the `expo-web-browser` import from `useGoogleAuth.tsx` (no longer needed for Google auth; keep the plugin in app.json if used elsewhere)\n\n## Part 2: Auth Error Observability\n\n### 2a. Add auth error constants to `errorParser.ts`\n\nExtend `ERROR_MESSAGES` with:\n\n```typescript\n// Auth - Google\nGOOGLE_AUTH_FAILED: \"Google sign-in failed. Please try again.\",\nGOOGLE_AUTH_CANCELLED: null, // silent — user chose to cancel\n\n// Auth - Apple\nAPPLE_AUTH_FAILED: \"Apple sign-in failed. Please try again.\",\nAPPLE_AUTH_NO_DATA: \"Apple didn't share your info. Go to Settings > Apple ID > Sign-In & Security > Sign in with Apple, remove Kindred, then try again.\",\n\n// Auth - General\nACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND_GOOGLE: \"No account found with this Google account. Sign up first!\",\nACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND_APPLE: \"No account found with this Apple ID. Sign up first!\",\nACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND_PHONE: \"No account found with this phone number. Sign up first!\",\nDUPLICATE_ACCOUNT: \"An account already exists with this sign-in method. Try signing in instead.\",\nOTP_INVALID: \"Invalid or expired code. Please try again.\",\nOTP_SEND_FAILED: \"Couldn't send verification code. Please try again.\",\n```\n\n### 2b. Replace `alert()` with `showToast()` in auth flows\n\n**Files to change:**\n\n1. **`OnboardModal.tsx`** — Apple register/login error handlers, Google `onError` callback\n2. **`useAuth.tsx`** — `login()`, `loginWithGoogle()`, `loginWithPhone()`, `loginWithOTP()`, `register()`, `registerWithGoogle()`\n\nPattern:\n```typescript\n// Before\nalert(\"Google authentication failed. Please try again.\");\n\n// After\nshowToast(ERROR_MESSAGES.GOOGLE_AUTH_FAILED, \"danger\", \"Sign-In Failed\");\n```\n\nFor cancellations (user dismisses auth), do nothing — no toast needed.\n\n### 2c. Add `Sentry.captureException()` to all auth error paths\n\nEvery `catch` block in auth flows gets a Sentry capture with context:\n\n```typescript\nimport * as Sentry from \"@sentry/react-native\";\n\n// In catch blocks:\nSentry.captureException(error, {\n  tags: {\n    \"auth.method\": \"google\",  // or \"apple\", \"phone\", \"otp\"\n    \"auth.flow\": \"login\",     // or \"register\"\n  },\n  extra: {\n    // any relevant non-PII context (e.g. error code, HTTP status)\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Do NOT capture cancellations** — only actual failures.\n\n**Files to change:**\n\n1. **`useAuth.tsx`** — all 6 auth functions (`login`, `loginWithGoogle`, `loginWithPhone`, `loginWithOTP`, `register`, `registerWithGoogle`)\n2. **`OnboardModal.tsx`** — `apple_register()`, `apple_login()`, Google `onSuccess` error handler, Google `onError` callback\n\n## Files Changed (Summary)\n\n| File | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `frontend/hooks/useGoogleAuth.tsx` | Full rewrite to native SDK |\n| `frontend/components/modals/OnboardModal.tsx` | Fix opacity, replace `alert()` with `showToast()`, add Sentry captures |\n| `frontend/hooks/useAuth.tsx` | Replace `alert()` with `showToast()`, add Sentry captures |\n| `frontend/utils/errorParser.ts` | Add auth error constants |\n| `frontend/app.json` | Add `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin` config plugin |\n| `frontend/package.json` | Add `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin`, remove unused deps if any |\n| `GOOGLE_OAUTH_SETUP.md` | Delete (obsolete) |\n| `GOOGLE_OAUTH_EXPO_GO_TEST.md` | Delete (obsolete) |\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Android Google Sign-In (no Android client ID yet — noted in existing docs)\n- Changing the auth backend endpoints (already working)\n- Refactoring the overall auth architecture\n- Adding retry logic or offline queuing\n\n## Requires\n\n- Native rebuild via EAS after merging (the native SDK config plugin 