            "content": "# Native Google Sign-In + Auth Error Observability\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Replace `expo-auth-session` Google Sign-In with the native `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin` SDK, and add toast notifications + Sentry error capture to all auth flows.\n\n**Architecture:** The Google auth hook (`useGoogleAuth.tsx`) is rewritten to use the native SDK while keeping the same external interface so `OnboardModal.tsx` needs minimal wiring changes. All auth error paths across Google, Apple, and Phone/OTP flows get `showToast()` instead of `alert()` and `Sentry.captureException()` with auth-specific tags. New error constants are added to the existing `errorParser.ts`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin`, `@sentry/react-native`, `react-native-toastable` (existing), Expo config plugins\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Install `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin` and configure\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `frontend/package.json`\n- Modify: `frontend/app.json:71-177` (plugins array)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Install the package**\n\nRun:\n```bash\ncd /Users/abhik.ray/Kindred/frontend && bun add @react-native-google-signin/google-signin\n```\n\nExpected: Package added to `package.json` dependencies.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add Expo config plugin to `app.json`**\n\nIn `frontend/app.json`, add to the `plugins` array (after `\"expo-web-browser\"`):\n\n```json\n[\"@react-native-google-signin/google-signin\", {\n  \"iosUrlScheme\": \"com.googleusercontent.apps.955300435674-4unacg9mbosj1sdf3gqb17lb6rasqmj6\"\n}]\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Remove the Google redirect scheme from `app.json`**\n\nThe `scheme` array currently has the Google reversed client ID for `expo-auth-session` redirects. The native SDK doesn't need it as a top-level scheme — the