            "content": "# Sentry Request Context Enrichment\n\n**Date:** 2026-05-06\n**Status:** Approved\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd a Fiber middleware that creates request-scoped Sentry hubs with rich context, and update the existing `SentryHandler` to use them. Every `slog.Error()` and `sentry.CaptureException()` call during a request will automatically include endpoint, user, and request metadata — no handler changes needed.\n\n## Problem\n\nToday, `SentryHandler` in `xslog/sentry.go` captures `slog.Error()` calls via `sentry.CurrentHub()` (global hub). Sentry events contain the error message and slog attributes but zero request context: no endpoint, no user, no HTTP method, no status code, no request duration. The Fiber error handler and panic recovery add some context (method, path, IP) but only fire on unhandled 500s and panics, not on the many `slog.Error()` calls throughout handlers.\n\n## Design\n\n### New file: `internal/xsentry/middleware.go`\n\nA Fiber middleware that runs on **all routes**, placed after panic recovery and before auth/PostHog.\n\n**Before `c.Next()`:**\n1. Clone the global Sentry hub → request-scoped hub\n2. Set request context on the scope:\n   - Tag `http.method` = `c.Method()`\n   - Tag `http.route` = `c.Route().Path` (pattern like `/v1/user/:id/tasks`)\n   - Sentry request context: URL (`c.OriginalURL()`), method, IP (`c.IP()`), user-agent (`c.Get(\"User-Agent\")`)\n3. Store the hub in Go context via `sentry.SetHubOnContext()` + `c.SetUserContext()`\n4. Record `startTime`\n\n**After `c.Next()` returns:**\n1. Compute duration\n2. Read status code from `c.Response().StatusCode()`\n3. Set tag `http.status_code`\n4. Set extra `duration_ms`\n5. If user_id is in context (auth middleware ran), set Sentry user (`scope.SetUser(sentry.User{ID: userID})`) and tag `user.timezone`\n6. For 4xx/5xx, capture truncated error response body as extra context\n\n**Context key:** Use `sentry.SetHubOnContext(ctx, hub)` / `sentry.GetHubFromContext(ctx)` — Sentry's built-in context plumbing, no custom keys needed.\n\n### Modified file: `internal/xslog/sentry.go`\n\nUpdate `reportToSentry()` to accept `ctx context.Context` (it already receives it in `Handle()`), and try `sentry.GetHubFromContext(ctx)` first. Fall back to `sentry.CurrentHub()` for errors outside HTTP requests (cron jobs, startup).\n\nThe `Handle()` method already receives `ctx` — it just doesn't pass it to `reportToSentry()` today. One signature change.\n\n### Modified file: `internal/server/server.go`\n\n1. Add `xsentry.FiberMiddleware()` after panic recovery, before CORS/auth/PostHog\n2. Simplify the Fiber error handler — remove the manual `hub.WithScope()` block since the middleware already sets request context on the scope. Just call `hub.CaptureException(err)`.\n3. Simplify the panic recovery `StackTraceHandler` similarly.\n\n## What a Sentry event looks like after this\n\n```\nException: \"Error creating waitlist entry\"\nLevel: error\n\nTags:\n  http.method: POST\n  http.route: /v1/waitlist\n  http.status_code: 500\n  logger: slog\n  user.timezone: America/New_York  (if authenticated)\n\nUser:\n  ID: 6789abc...  (if authenticated)\n\nRequest:\n  URL: /v1/waitlist?ref=abc\n  Method: POST\n  IP: 192.168.1.1\n  User-Agent: Kindred/1.0 iOS\n\nExtra:\n  duration_ms: 142\n  error: \"mongo: duplicate key\"\n  email: \"user@example.com\"  (from slog attributes)\n```\n\n## Files Changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `internal/xsentry/middleware.go` | **New** — Fiber middleware |\n| `internal/xslog/sentry.go` | Use request-scoped hub from context |\n| `internal/server/server.go` | Wire middleware, simplify error handler + panic recovery |\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Changing handler error patterns (they already work — this is additive)\n- Adding Sentry to individual handlers (the middleware makes this unnecessary)\n- Performance tracing / spans (separate concern)\n- Modifying PostHog middleware\n",
